14/03/2007
ZAGREB, Croatia -- Authorities in Vienna confirmed on Tuesday (March 13th) that they have detained former Croatian Deputy Defence Minister Vladimir Zagorec on corruption charges. 
He was arrested on the basis of an international arrest warrant issued by Croatia, which accuses him of misappropriating $5m from the Defence Ministry during the former Yugoslav conflicts. 
General Zagorec was responsible for supplying weapons to the Croatian Army. 
(Vecernji list - 14/03/07; HINA, RTS - 13/03/07)
